Flying to Chuhuiv, Kharkiv Oblast
Flying to Chuhuiv, Kharkiv Oblast
Disappeared west of Kupyansk, Kharkiv Oblast.

A second Tu-95MS has departed from Engels-2 Airbase. It is unclear if this took off at the same time as the first Tu-95 around 35 minutes ago, or if this only just occurred. Either way, this is expected to be the last Tu-95 to depart from there. 1 other Tu‚Ä¶
The other Tu-160 stationed at Engels-2 Airbase is not expected to take off tonight.

This is approximately what the map looks like so far regarding missiles. 
2 Kinzhals, impacting between Fastiv and Irpin, Kyiv Oblast.
1 Iskander-M, impacting northwest of Kupyansk, Kharkiv Oblast.

The Tu-95s did indeed change course to Nizhny Novgorod Oblast, where they will launch cruise missiles from launch lines further east. Cruise missiles are expected to arrive in Ukrainian airspace in less than 2 hours from now.
Around 130 Geran-2 drones are now recorded in Ukrainian airspace following the repeated launches earlier.
Around 130 Geran-2 drones are now recorded in Ukrainian airspace following the repeated launches earlier.
Some of these new drones are attacking targets in Kharkiv City. At least 5 impacts have been recorded within the city limits so far. More are flying in.
The 2 Tu-95MS from Engels-2 Airbase conducted a launch maneuver from Engels District, Saratov Oblast.
The 2 Tu-95MS from Engels-2 Airbase conducted a launch maneuver from Engels District, Saratov Oblast.
Keep in mind, these launches could have been simulated. If they were real, then they are expected to arrive in Ukrainian airspace in 50-70 minutes.
The 2 Tu-95MS from Engels-2 Airbase conducted a launch maneuver from Engels District, Saratov Oblast.

It seems these bombers used new launch lines too. They carried out launch maneuvers from the northeastern part of Saratov Oblast, around 200km from the usual launch lines in Engels District of Saratov Oblast.
The 3 Tu-95MS from Olenya Airbase also carried out launch maneuvers.
The 3 Tu-95MS from Olenya Airbase also carried out launch maneuvers.
These ones changed course away from Nizhny Novgorod Oblast, and carried out launch maneuvers from one of the normal launch lines in Mokshansky District, Penza Oblast.
Kalibr launches were recorded from ships in the Black Sea / Sea of Azov.
Kalibr launches were recorded from ships in the Black Sea / Sea of Azov.
4-6 missiles were launched from the submarine off the coast of Anapa, Krasnodar Krai.
Iskander launches will likely take place in the near future.
The Kalibrs are expected to enter Ukrainian airspace via the Beryslav District of Kherson Oblast.
~40 Geran-2 drones are flying to attack targets in Kyiv Oblast.
The first Kalibrs flew over the Kinburn Spit, flying towards Kherson City / Beryslav District.

Now flying towards Ochakiv, Mykolaiv Oblast.
Now flying towards Ochakiv, Mykolaiv Oblast.
The first 4 Kalibrs entered Ukrainian airspace near Dmytrivka, Mykolaiv Oblast flying northwest. I will start posting live maps soon.

In Video: Russian Interceptor Hits Ukrainian FPV Drone Carrier
The Russian military has shot down a Ukrainian Ukrspecsystems PD-2 fixed-wing drone carrying FPV suicide drones with an interceptor drone over the special military operation zone.
RIA Novosti shared footage of the successful interception on July 20. The interceptor used to take down the drone carrier was a version of the Boomerang, an FPV quadcopter known for its high maneuverability, its ability to fly at speeds up to 170 kilometers per hour and its high resistance to jamming.
The PD-2 was carrying two FPV quadcopter drones under its wings, apparently on an attack mission, when the Boomerang directly hit its propeller.

Ukraine Defies Trump, Strikes Moscow: Chronicle Of The Four-Day Aerial Confrontation 
Despite statements from the U.S. administration deeming attacks on the Russian capital unacceptable, Ukrainian drones have persisted in attempting to breach Moscow's defenses for the fourth consecutive day. Moscow's airports have activated the ‚ÄúCarpet‚Äù security protocol, resulting in the delay of hundreds of flights and train services. Meanwhile, a German general, Christian Freuding, has publicly called for continued strikes on Russian airfields and defense industry facilities.
From the evening of July 17 to Sunday, July 20, the Russia-Ukraine conflict saw a sharp escalation in mutual strikes. Ukraine launched drone attacks on Moscow and surrounding areas for several consecutive nights, marking the most significant assault on the capital region since the conflict began. Simultaneously, Russian forces executed large-scale missile and drone attacks on Ukrainian cities and infrastructure.

Pro-Government Forces Violate Ceasefire In Al-Suwayda With New Offensive (Videos)
Tribal forces loyal to Syria‚Äôs Islamist-led government launched a new offensive against Druze fighters in the southern governorate of al-Suwayda on July 20 afternoon, violating a ceasefire brokered by the United States just two days earlier.
The forces, which reportedly include government troops, attacked the town of Ariqah and nearby areas in the northern countryside of al-Suwayda. Heavy weapons, including mortars, rockets and large-caliber guns, were reported used by the attackers. Still, Druze fighters shield onto their positions in the town and managed to capture some tribesmen.
The attack started around the same time the tribes and the Druze were supposed to exchange captives, one of the key terms of the ceasefire announced by the U.S. after talks with both Syria and Israel, which has been backing Druze fighters.
